TEXT(beginproblem());

############################################################
# PG Setup Code
############################################################
Context("ImplicitEquation");
Context()->variables->are(x=>'Real');
$a = random(1,10,1);
$b = random(-10,-1,1);
$solstring = "(x-$a)*(x-$b)*(x-2/3)=0";
$solution = ImplicitEquation($solstring);

$evaluator = $solution->cmp(
     cmp_class=>'a cubic equation',
     correct_ans=>$solstring,
     correct_ans_latex_string=>$solstring,
     checker => sub {
       my ($correct,$student,$ansHash) = @_;
       ($left, $right) = split('=',$ansHash->{original_student_ans});
       $left = Formula($left);
       $right= Formula($right);
       $ansHash->{preview_latex_string} = $ansHash->{original_student_ans};
       $ansHash->{preview_text_string} = $ansHash->{original_student_ans};
       $ansHash->{student_ans} = $ansHash->{original_student_ans};
       return ($correct == $student);
     }
   );

############################################################
# Body
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML
Give an example of a cubic equation that has three solutions: one solution is [`x = [$a]\text{,}`] the second solution is [`x= [$b]\text{,}`] and the third solution is [` x = \frac{2}{3} \text{.}`] Write your equation in standard form.

[_]{$evaluator}{30}

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
I will first write a cubic equation in factored form: [` (x-a)(x-b)(x-c) = 0 `] where [`a,
                b\text{,}`] and [`c`] are the solutions of the equation. Thus, we can write the cubic equation as [` (x-[$a])(x-([$b]))(x - \frac{2}{3}) = 0 `] or [` (x-[$a])(x-[$b])(x - \frac{2}{3}) = 0 \text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

